oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Josephus Conn Guild
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Portrait of Judge Josephus Conn Guild (1802-1883).
He married Catherine Blackmore in 1826 and had five children. He served in the Seminole War and was promoted to colonel. He was elected a member of the House for the 20 and 21st General Assemblies.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
